od. Sure to be controversial, this book is a major intervention in the scholarship on slavery, economic development, and political power in early British America, mounting a powerful and original argument that boldly challenges historical orthodoxy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPlantationszJamaicaxHistory. 0aPlantationszNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aSlaveryzNorth AmericaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  abritish, americas, american, plantation, slaves, slavery, history, philosophy, violence, economics, racial divisions, racism, political power, north america, colonialism, imperialism, jamaica, colonial period, colonies, white solidarity, planter elites, wealth, revolution, costs, united states, humanity, chattel, enslavement, european, slaveowners.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226286242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226286242/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles